```

2. Open the `Pages\Account\Manage\EnableAuthenticator.cshtml.cs` and search for the following line, inside the `OnGetAsync()` method;

```C#
await LoadSharedKeyAndQrCodeUriAsync(user);
```

Remove the code shown below which follows the call to `LoadSharedKeyAndQrCodeUriAsync(user);`

```C#
if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(SharedKey))		
{		
    await _userManager.ResetAuthenticatorKeyAsync(user);		
    await LoadSharedKeyAndQrCodeUriAsync(user);		
}
```

The `OnGetAsync()` method should now look like

```C#
public async Task<IActionResult> OnGetAsync()
{
    var user = await _userManager.GetUserAsync(User);
    if (user == null)
    {
        throw new ApplicationException($"Unable to load user with ID '{_userManager.GetUserId(User)}'.");
    }

    await LoadSharedKeyAndQrCodeUriAsync(user);

    return Page();
}
```

